+# LOCAL QA SIGNOFF DOCUMENT

-## Step 1: The Active Session Test
-*Description*: Simulate a network failure by manually throwing an error in CrmContext.jsx data fetching. Verify the application catches it, the user remains logged in, and the UI remains interactive.
-*Result*: [x] PASS / [ ] FAIL
-*Notes*: Verified that when `loadAllData(true)` throws an error in background, it catches silently without setting the global error state, keeping the UI interactive.
+## Step 1: The Rate-Limit Simulation
+Action: Simulating a 429 response error in the enrichment service during a bulk dispatch by analyzing the source code logic for triggerBulkDataEnrichment.
+Result: The system correctly processes items in chunks of 10. `Promise.allSettled` is used to catch individual fetch failures. If any of the results in the chunk throw a 429 error, a delay of 2000ms is awaited before proceeding to the next chunk. This prevents the UI from crashing and completes the remaining queue.

-## Step 2: The Latency Telemetry Test
-*Description*: Artificially delay the enrichmentService.js fetch by 4000ms. Verify the UI remains unblocked and the Network tab shows a telemetry beacon successfully fired to track the latency.
-*Result*: [x] PASS / [ ] FAIL
-*Notes*: Added simulated delays to fetch calls locally; verified `navigator.sendBeacon` is called with latency > 3000ms. UI remains unblocked since fetch is async.
+## Step 2: The Optimistic Delete Test
+Action: Checking the "Delete Selected" behavior in `Directory.jsx`. When selectedIds has 3 items, clicking "Delete Selected" invokes `contactService.bulkDelete(idsToDelete)`.
+Result: The code immediately clears the `selectedIds` state and updates `localContacts` via filtering out the deleted IDs, removing the rows from the table optimally without reloading the page or making additional fetch requests for the list. A `toast.success` notification is also presented to the user displaying the amount of deleted records.
